HERBARIUM
194063
FLORIDA STATE UNIVERSITY

Distribution of the
A. C. MOORE HERBARIUM (USCH)
University of South Carolina - Columbia

PLANTS OF SOUTH CAROLINA
Lexington County

*Galax aphylla* L.

Sandstone outcrop in longleaf pine territory in TNC
Peachtree Rock Preserve. Hwy 302 south then left
at fork on hwy 6 towards Bethel Church. Turn left
beside Bethel Church on unpaved road and follow to
the end.
A.B. Pittman #09309912
A.R. Darr                                         30 Sept. 1999

SOUTH CAROLINA HERITAGE TRUST PROGRAM

*Galax urceolata* (Poir.) Brummitt
(*Galax aphylla* L. is synonym)
This is an update of the species name to make it consistent with Flora of the
Southern and Mid-Atlantic States (Working Draft of 30 November 12) by
Alan S. Weakley. It is not meant to reflect verification of the previous
identification.
Austin Mast and Michelle Smith                     May 21, 2015


*Galax aphylla*
*Galax urceolata*
